    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-08-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="336" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Kreismann</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 9.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,
                                        <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-08-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 5, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>S<hi rend="smallcaps">ir:</hi> * * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>The outbreak in New York, amidst all the cheering successes of our arms,
                            is indeed a sad and disgraceful affair; but the determination of the
                            government to maintain the supremacy of the laws, and to enforce them,
                            will make it subserve the interests and triumph of our cause.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>H. KREISMANN.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William</hi> H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, &amp;c.,
                                    &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
